OL,6,FHaving refused a breathalyser test at
OL,7,Fthe roadside, Mackay was arrested, and
OL,8,Fhis blood was tested instead.
OL,10,FHe was found to have been driving
OL,11,Fwhilst two and half times over the
OL,12,Fdrug drive limit, and more than two
OL,13,Ftimes over the limit for drink
OL,14,Fdriving, with his blood showing 172
OL,15,Fmilligrams of alcohol whilst the legal
OL,16,Flimit is 80 milligrams.
OL,18,FOfficers were able to use DNA to place
OL,19,FMackay in the driver's seat at the
OL,20,Ftime of the collision.
